                 xml:id="EIAD0092_textPart1">
					          <ab>
						            <lb n="1"/>
						            <w xml:id="tok4529">bu</w>
						            <w xml:id="tok4530">
                     <unclear>na</unclear>
                  </w>
						            <lb n="2"/>
						            <w xml:id="tok4531">hathikasa</w>
						            <lb n="3"/>
						            <w xml:id="tok4532">budharakhitasa</w>
					          </ab>
				        </div>
				        <div type="textpart"
                 subtype="graffiti"
                 n="Block 2"
                 xml:id="EIAD0092_textPart2">
					          <ab>
						            <w xml:id="tok4533">nagutara</w>
					          </ab>
				        </div>
			      </div>
				     <div type="apparatus">
					       <listApp corresp="#EIAD0092_textPart1">
						         <app loc="1">
							           <lem>bu <unclear>na</unclear>
                  </lem>
							           <rdg source="eiad-bibl:Raghunath2001">bu … </rdg>
							           <note>This could could possibly be an abbreviation
								for <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">buddhāya
									namo</foreign>.</note>
						         </app>
					       </listApp>
				     </div>
				     <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
					       <p>Veneration to the Buddha (?). Of the <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">hathika</foreign> (?)
						Budharakhita (Buddharakṣita).</p>
					       <p>Nagutara (Nāgottara).</p>
				     </div>
				     <!--<div type="commentary"></div>-->
				     <div type="bibliography">
					       <p>The three graffiti of block 1 noticed in <bibl>
							           <ptr target="eiad-bibl:zoteroItem_G9CH6AGA"/>
							           <citedRange>1959-60</citedRange>
						         </bibl>. The fourth graffito, or block 2, perpendicular to the
						others, was added in <bibl>
							           <ptr target="eiad-bibl:zoteroItem_G9CH6AGA"/>
							           <citedRange>1976-77: B.2</citedRange>
						         </bibl>. Re-edited here from available documentation and
						after autopsy of the stone.</p>
					       <listBibl type="secondary-bibliography">
						         <bibl>
							           <ptr target="eiad-bibl:Raghunath2001"/>:
								<citedRange>189 (no. 73)</citedRange>
						         </bibl>
					       </listBibl>
				     </div>
